<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB4EF77FF42FD3AFC30FC3A" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB4EF77FF42FD3AFC30FC3A" blockId="28.[151,1437,582,898]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FF42FD3AFEE7FD11" bold="true" box="[199,338,655,681]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Comments:</emphasis>
The taxonomic interpretation of this species is tricky, as the species needs to be revised (Cadena- Castañeda, 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FE9FFD01FEFFFD75" box="[282,330,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">pers</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FEDFFD01FE28FD75" box="[346,413,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">comm</emphasis>
.), what also makes the interpretation of its distribution quite complicated. The individual not even runs to 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FED4FD6DFE1BFD49" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1862" box="[337,430,728,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Dysonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FED4FD6DFE1BFD49" box="[337,430,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Dysonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key for the genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FC96FD6DFCC5FD49" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1862" box="[787,880,728,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Dysonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FC96FD6DFCC5FD49" box="[787,880,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Dysonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FBF1FD62FA2DFD49" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[1140,1432,727,753]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="51 - 60" refId="ref29573" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2011) La tribu Dysoniini parte I: El complejo Dysonia (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) y su nueva organizacion taxonomica. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 20, 51 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1665 / 034.020.0105" type="journal article" year="2011">Cadena-Castañeda (2011)</bibRefCitation>
: it presents the pronotum with lateral margin expanded, and carinae of the metazona elevated, besides the reduced spines on the posterior femora, running to the genera 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FD7FFCAAFB0DFC81" authority="Cadena-Castaneda, 2011" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" box="[762,1208,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodentix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FD7FFCAAFC2CFC81" box="[762,921,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Lichenodentix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FC24FCAAFB0DFC81" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[929,1208,799,825]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="51 - 60" refId="ref29573" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2011) La tribu Dysoniini parte I: El complejo Dysonia (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) y su nueva organizacion taxonomica. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 20, 51 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1665 / 034.020.0105" type="journal article" year="2011">Cadena-Castañeda, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FB65FCAAFE04FCE5" authority="Cadena-Castaneda, 2011" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FB65FCAAFA29FC81" box="[1248,1436,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Lichenomorphus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FF12FCF6FE04FCE5" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[151,433,835,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="51 - 60" refId="ref29573" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2011) La tribu Dysoniini parte I: El complejo Dysonia (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) y su nueva organizacion taxonomica. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 20, 51 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1665 / 034.020.0105" type="journal article" year="2011">Cadena-Castañeda, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the individual presents pronotum without teethed borders (as in 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FA89FCF6FF79FC39" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FA89FCF6FF79FC39" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Lichenomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and subgenital plate smaller than cerci (as in 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FD53FCD2FCC0FC39" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" box="[726,885,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenodentix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FD53FCD2FCC0FC39" box="[726,885,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Lichenodentix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
